'''游戏成瘾'''（英文：Video game addiction，缩写：VGA）是一种特殊的[[成瘾行为|成瘾行为]]，其特征为过度或强迫性游戏以致影响正常生活。目前游戏成瘾的定义在医学界仍是极具争议的，没有确切的证据表明游戏成瘾应当被归类为精神疾病。<ref>Hauge, Marney R. and Douglas A. Gentile. [http://www.psychology.iastate.edu/faculty/dgentile/SRCD%20Video%20Game%20Addiction.pdf Video game addiction among adolescents: Associations with academic performance and aggression.] {{Wayback|url=http://www.psychology.iastate.edu/faculty/dgentile/SRCD%20Video%20Game%20Addiction.pdf |date=20090407085048 }} Paper presented at a Society for Research in Child Development Conference, Tampa Florida.  April, 2003. Retrieved June 25, 2007.</ref><ref name="Tanner2007">{{cite news|url=http://www.msnbc.msn.com/id/19354827/|title=Is video-game addiction a mental disorder?|last=Tanner|first=Lindsey|date=2007-06-22|agency=Associated Press|accessdate=2009-05-09|archive-date=2008-05-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080511173735/http://www.msnbc.msn.com/id/19354827/|dead-url=no}}</ref>2010年，有媒体报道称《[[精神疾病診斷與統計手冊|精神疾病诊断与统计手册]]》（缩写：DSM）中可能会考虑收录游戏成瘾。但[[美国精神医学学会|美国精神医学学会]]发表的声明表示没有将游戏成瘾列为精神疾病，修订DSM是一件长期的、严肃的事情，所有的更改都将基于最新且可靠的科学研究。<ref name="notenough1">{{cite web|url=http://www.sciencedaily.com/releases/2007/06/070625133354.htm|title=American Psychiatric Association Considers 'Video Game Addiction'|date=2007-06-25|publisher=[[Science_Daily|Science Daily]]|access-date=2010-09-26|archive-date=2021-02-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210211203415/https://www.sciencedaily.com/releases/2007/06/070625133354.htm|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="notenough2">{{cite news|url=http://www.foxnews.com/printer_friendly_story/0,3566,286948,00.html|title=AMA Will Not Label Video-Game Playing as a Psychiatric Addiction|date=2007-06-28|publisher=[[Fox_News_(disambiguation)|FoxNews.com]]|accessdate=2010-09-26|archive-date=2021-05-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210511215038/https://www.foxnews.com/printer_friendly_story/0,3566,286948,00.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>Nguyen, Katherine “Video game addiction all too real.” OC Register Sunday, January 28, 2007</ref>2019年5月，[[世界卫生组织|世界卫生组织]]将游戏成瘾列入[[國際疾病與相關健康問題統計分類|国际疾病与相关健康问题统计分类]]。

== 医学界观点 ==
游戏成瘾的定性在医学界并未获得共识，比如美国精神医学学会认为现有证据不足以证明游戏成瘾是一种精神疾病，并拒绝在第5版（2013年5月）《精神疾病诊断与统计手册》中收录游戏成瘾。<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://dsm.psychiatryonline.org/doi/book/10.1176/appi.books.9780890425596|title=Conditions for Further Study|accessdate=2018-06-27|author=|date=|publisher=American Psychiatric Association .|archive-date=2019-12-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191212191252/https://dsm.psychiatryonline.org/doi/book/10.1176/appi.books.9780890425596|dead-url=no}}</ref>而[[联合国|联合国]][[世界卫生组织|世界卫生组织]]则持不同态度，<ref>{{cite web|title=游戏成瘾变精神病？都是国内媒体误传|url=http://tech.ifeng.com/a/20171114/44760861_0.shtml|website=凤凰网·科技|accessdate=2017-11-14|archive-date=2019-06-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190604143035/http://tech.ifeng.com/a/20171114/44760861_0.shtml|dead-url=no}}</ref>并在2018年6月将“游戏障碍”{{NoteTag|此处卫生组织使用的是“Gaming Disorder”，即“游戏障碍”<ref>{{Cite web |url = https://www.who.int/features/qa/gaming-disorder/zh/ |title = 游戏障碍 |author =  |date = 2018-09 |publisher = 世界卫生组织 |language = zh-cn |accessdate = 2020-01-24 |archive-date = 2020-10-19 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201019025220/https://www.who.int/features/qa/gaming-disorder/zh/ |dead-url = no }}</ref>，而非“成瘾”。}}收录至[[第十一版國際疾病分類|第十一版国际疾病分类]]（缩写：ICD-11'''）'''。<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://icd.who.int/browse11/l-m/en|title=ICD-11 - Mortality and Morbidity Statistics|accessdate=2018-06-20|work=世界卫生组织|language=en|archive-date=2018-08-01|archive-url=https://archive.today/20180801205234/https://icd.who.int/browse11/l-m/en%23/http://id.who.int/icd/entity/294762853|dead-url=no}}</ref>但世界卫生组织这一行为亦引起许多批评与不满，在ICD-11正式批准前，{{NoteTag|ICD-11于2018年6月发布的版本仅为预览版本，正式生效时间为2022年1月1日。}}26位研究者撰写一封致世界卫生组织的公开信，表示其提出的诊断分类缺乏科学证据，可能造成更多害处而非好处。<ref>{{Cite journal|title=Scholars’ open debate paper on the World Health Organization ICD-11 Gaming Disorder proposal|url=http://www.akademiai.com/doi/pdf/10.1556/2006.5.2016.088|last=Aarseth|first=Espen|last2=Bean|first2=Anthony M.|date=2017-09|journal=Journal of Behavioral Addictions|issue=3|doi=10.1556/2006.5.2016.088|volume=6|pages=267–270|language=en|issn=2062-5871|pmc=5700734|pmid=28033714|last3=Boonen|first3=Huub|last4=Colder Carras|first4=Michelle|last5=Coulson|first5=Mark|last6=Das|first6=Dimitri|last7=Deleuze|first7=Jory|last8=Dunkels|first8=Elza|last9=Edman|first9=Johan|access-date=2018-06-27|archive-date=2019-08-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190813012201/https://akademiai.com/doi/pdf/10.1556/2006.5.2016.088|dead-url=no}}</ref>与此同时，诸多游戏协会亦提出反对，指出“[[遊戲障礙|遊戲障礙]]”在医学界仍是存在争议与不确定性的。<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.gamasutra.com/view/news/320260/Games_industry_trade_bodies_concerned_by_gaming_disorder_classification__.php|title=Games industry trade bodies concerned by 'gaming disorder' classification|last=Kerr|first=Chris|accessdate=2018-06-27|language=en|archive-date=2018-06-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180619213900/https://www.gamasutra.com/view/news/320260/Games_industry_trade_bodies_concerned_by_gaming_disorder_classification__.php|dead-url=no}}</ref>

==可能致病成因==
一些人認為，遊戲裡內建的[[獎勵|獎勵制度]]，可能是導致遊戲成癮的原因。<ref>Haggard, Daniel.  [http://danielhaggard.com/24/the-computer-game-affliction-how-they-addict-you/ The computer game affliction: how they addict you.] {{Wayback|url=http://danielhaggard.com/24/the-computer-game-affliction-how-they-addict-you/ |date=20070410040008 }}. Retrieved June 25, 2007.</ref><ref>LeClaire, Jennifer. [http://www.technewsworld.com/story/52916.html Warning Signs Appear Along Road to Video Game Addiction] {{WebCite|url=https://www.webcitation.org/6qzMvxcoa?url=http://www.technewsworld.com/story/52916.html |date=20170605081338 |dateformat=iso }} TechNews World. September 13, 2006. Retrieved June 25, 2007.</ref>
 
在遊戲所創造的[[虛擬世界|虛擬世界]]中，游戏成瘾者能獲得無法在現實世界中得到的[[自信|自信]]與[[滿足|滿足感]]。

